@galen-pivotal / @dschneider-pivotal: first of all, thanks for taking the time to review the changes. Considering that a lot of changes I made are flaky, and the following statement:

> Only a single thread updates the stats on these classes. Other parts of them (like the HashMap instances) are not thread safe. I think the volatiles existed just to make sure readers of the stats saw that last value recorded. So consider if you want to keep pursuing this change.

I'll revert the modified classes to what they were, only adding small changes within the order of the methods declaration and removal of some warnings + the addition of the JUnit tests. Sounds good?.
